{"TopicId":175017,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Airplanes nose pinching problem. Help please!","CreatedByName":"SoulReaper1702","CreatedById":188977,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-16T20:50:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SoulReaper1702","CreatedById":188977,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-16T20:50:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am having trouble with the pitch of my plane. The plane takes off perfectly however 3-4 seconds after launch the airplane tilts down. I have tried moving the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E but that doesnt seem to help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-16T21:54:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380150\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526503813\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188977\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SoulReaper1702\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, SoulReaper1702 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am having trouble with the pitch of my plane. The plane takes off perfectly however 3-4 seconds after launch the airplane tilts down. I have tried moving the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E but that doesnt seem to help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow about pics of the plane in question?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-16T22:00:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E back relative to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E should increase the pitch-down moment, so that would not be expected to help. I would assume that what you need is more restoring force from your tail. You probably don\u0027t have enough control authority in your elevators.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe plane is like a lever, with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E as the pivot. You need the forces to balance on both sides of the pivot. If your plane is pitching down, then you need to either move the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E back (not forward) or you need to get more downforce (or less lift) from the tail.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are using canards, then it means you need to either get more lift from your canards or you need to move your main wing a little forward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-16T22:24:58Z\u0022 title=\u002205/16/2018 10:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 16, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by mikegarrison\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-16T22:50:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380150\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526503813\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188977\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SoulReaper1702\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, SoulReaper1702 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am having trouble with the pitch of my plane. The plane takes off perfectly however 3-4 seconds after launch the airplane tilts down. I have tried moving the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E but that doesnt seem to help. \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can do a couple of things while in flight. Do a right click on your tail fins and play with the limiter settings. Sometimes manually adjusting them until the indicator on the nav ball indicates a \u002B5 degree will solve the problem. What would help me help you better is for a few screen shots of your craft - one in the hangar with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator on and then one in flight as your plane pitches down. If you can do that, I\u0027ll give it my best shot at diagnosing it for you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SoulReaper1702","CreatedById":188977,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T02:20:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380230\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526511033\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can do a couple of things while in flight. Do a right click on your tail fins and play with the limiter settings. Sometimes manually adjusting them until the indicator on the nav ball indicates a \u002B5 degree will solve the problem. What would help me help you better is for a few screen shots of your craft - one in the hangar with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator on and then one in flight as your plane pitches down. If you can do that, I\u0027ll give it my best shot at diagnosing it for you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLink to a picture from the side.\uFEFF\uFEFF\uFEFF\uFEFF\uFEFF\uFEFF\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/open?id=1S_uOaos8VBGgmi2hHpjEr1Vu6gkJVePs\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/open?\uFEFFid=1S_uOaos8VBGgmi2hHpjEr1Vu6gkJVePs\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLink to a picture from the top\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/open?id=1DGfh6jr89ocmcqzIX4PMI3cZYtqhrkOU\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/open?\uFEFFid=1DGfh6jr89ocmcqzIX4PMI3cZYtqhrkOU\uFEFF\uFEFF\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T03:58:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E is so close to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E that the plane is having trouble exerting torque to apply control authority. That\u0027s going to cause trouble on any axis and it just happens that in this case it\u0027s nosing down. Counter-intuitively, I believe shifting the wings back slightly would help. Although that would make the plane more nose-heavy, it will also help the control surfaces do their job.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, now that it\u0027s clear your question is about a KSP craft, the thread has been moved to Gameplay Questions.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Val","CreatedById":126227,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T08:07:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think another\u00A0issue could be the control surface that you\u0027ve added to the swept wings. It appears that the axis of rotation for the control surfaces crosses the centerline in front of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, which used to cause them to work opposite direction of what you want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022t3PExMh.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022547\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/t3PExMh.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SoulReaper1702","CreatedById":188977,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T10:47:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380368\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526529501\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E is so close to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E that the plane is having trouble exerting torque to apply control authority. That\u0027s going to cause trouble on any axis and it just happens that in this case it\u0027s nosing down. Counter-intuitively, I believe shifting the wings back slightly would help. Although that would make the plane more nose-heavy, it will also help the control surfaces do their job.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, now that it\u0027s clear your question is about a KSP craft, the thread has been moved to Gameplay Questions.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will check that. So what I want is my \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SoulReaper1702","CreatedById":188977,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T10:48:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380461\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526544456\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Val\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Val said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think another\u00A0issue could be the control surface that you\u0027ve added to the swept wings. It appears that the axis of rotation for the control surfaces crosses the centerline in front of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, which used to cause them to work opposite direction of what you want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/t3PExMh.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022t3PExMh.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022547\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/t3PExMh.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do not understand. Are you talking about the elevators on the wings ?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T11:39:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380461\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526544456\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Val\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Val said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt appears that the axis of rotation for the control surfaces crosses the centerline in front of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, which used to cause them to work opposite direction of what you want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe\u0027s talking about this. When this happened to me, it took so much time to detect that I got sympathized with the fellow Kerbal and made this image\u00A0to make it clear. \u003Cspan\u003E:-) Essentially, my elevons became airbrakes! \u003Cspan\u003E:-D\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EOn the bright side, when having a odd number of\u00A0surfaces on my wings, I usually make two of them as airbrakes (attaching the deploy to the brake action, and reversing the deploy of one of them) and save two parts (symmetrical\u00A0airbrakes) on my designs. I had to learn something from this stunt! ;-)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022l4ONuD3lGkIuqh3gAfhGUM3Mxc2Kcrwl4hd-DoYE\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022275\u0022 src=\u0022https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/l4ONuD3lGkIuqh3gAfhGUM3Mxc2Kcrwl4hd-DoYEVUzzxlAnLyQXsIQxW-i6o5H1Mc_i4JEQ9J6kkcPCUG0CPyg0qDl-eR_NKCbznwZGjpxSNdIeePOumKhPzvS5rCNX5bf2pNVp6K9hQV09RYrHqkUKjSEudmfIu_MpSivU7HqLtksyXOBzHiMapLDM9Kk06Qmph3uJE8jqsI7h5Qg3Nftt0v2xf4f5wd-nju6sjlYQxEMUl1EAl4h9Q19smYJHCS85o-8d4bCassqNuufUAf4VcBv3hiiSUQED5vmSbKYIwIREzZIMuwJdt7miMT4WfJiUDvfDBI0F3AvVRtfhrhNG9GiXqNF0M_5avE7EDZYaP_XiZ-VpwOBbdOVtpV__KN5ZqPoK7snWO7qASyVRUn0oCp52ifpjqu1HWKip4Vf5qTZZef8zPBMSMupKbnWzdQy5b8qCx7snyCpGttxBUnnBkBMnYKx5mO5I1eMXFRtRTukVnbshJW-H3ggjDDlH6HXhoVWDGwFQkLQNjvdNTEeoTcJBxKNKIC-lahnbXStJkhF4SnPosPtDCIwcHiXxHSZ6iUlnZE4ByPC8Kr5kDHyecylqR0J4IXn8q6GrSlhJJq0FfIbDimud7AEmQSHPYEQcDVOOKn_95pR69G3I6RU9wczR6DVG=w574-h275-no\u0022 width=\u0022574\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn time, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/126227-val/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022126227\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/126227-val/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Val\u003C/a\u003E, since the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E usually moves as the fuel is consumed, would be more appropriate to make the elevons shift functions based on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E? This would make\u00A0things a bit more realistic - and logical, as the\u00A0rotation\u00A0pivot \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eis\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-17T12:45:46Z\u0022 title=\u002205/17/2018 12:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 17, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Lisias\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Ebeter phrasing\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Val","CreatedById":126227,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T12:39:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380523\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526557188\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lisias\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n54 minutes ago, Lisias said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn time, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/126227-val/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022126227\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/126227-val/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Val\u003C/a\u003E, since the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E usually moves as the fuel is consumed, would be more appropriate to make the elevons shift functions based on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt can\u0027t be based on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E, because\u00A0moving the control surfaces moves \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E. That is actually the whole purpose of control surfaces. Moving the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E around to make the craft change attitude.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KiozINr.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022340\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/KiozINr.gif\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n54 minutes ago, Lisias said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis wo\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Euld make\u00A0things a bit more realistic - and logical, as the\u00A0rotation\u00A0pivot \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eis\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo.\u00A0The pivot is \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T12:42:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380546\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526560781\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Val\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Val said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo.\u00A0The pivot is \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the explanation! (in time, what did you use to generate the animated images?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Val","CreatedById":126227,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T12:42:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380502\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526554086\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188977\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SoulReaper1702\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, SoulReaper1702 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do not understand. Are you talking about the elevators on the wings ?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. It is probably not the only problem you are having, but I think it\u0027s a contributing factor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380549\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526560956\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lisias\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Lisias said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the explanation! (in time, what did you use to generate the animated images?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI first recorded it as a video clip, then made it to a .gif with\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://gifmaker.me/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://gifmaker.me/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T13:11:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s my two cents, although it seems that the issue has already has been answered.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022X5Qzf69.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/X5Qzf69.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uTkV4z7.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/uTkV4z7.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn this example I\u0027ve given you, I try to keep the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E a little behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E. This way, the craft has a natural tendency to want to have upward drift rather than the alternative you\u0027ve experienced. In fact, here\u0027s my latest craft - the DC-7 (the bottom image is the real aircraft):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022qlLsEAq.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/qlLsEAq.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022d_abac.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022676\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.airlines-airliners.de/airliners/dc7/d_abac.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Val","CreatedById":126227,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T13:29:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380566\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526562698\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI try to keep the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E a little behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E. This way, the craft has a natural tendency to want to have upward drift rather than the alternative you\u0027ve experienced.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. If you place \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#00ffff;\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E behind \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffff00;\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E, then the craft will have a natural tendency to dive towards the ground unless some up elevator is applied.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T13:35:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380572\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526563756\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Val\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Val said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. If you place \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#00ffff;\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E behind \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffff00;\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E, then the craft will have a natural tendency to dive towards the ground unless some up elevator is applied.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor some reason, I\u0027m not having that problem... You\u0027re probably right and I\u0027ve found some sort of strange KSP physics flaw...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Val","CreatedById":126227,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T13:40:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526564120\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor some reason, I\u0027m not having that problem... You\u0027re probably right and I\u0027ve found some sort of strange KSP physics flaw...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery likely. As the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E doesn\u0027t take into account lift and drag from parts with no Lift rating. Which also means my statement is only accurate for crafts with very few non-Lift rating parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTorque from off center engine thrust can\u00A0also be a factor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SoulReaper1702","CreatedById":188977,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T13:53:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380578\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526564425\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Val\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Val said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery likely. As the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E doesn\u0027t take into account lift and drag from parts with no Lift rating. Which also means my statement is only accurate for crafts with very few non-Lift rating parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTorque from off center engine thrust can\u00A0also be a factor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what should I do val?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Val","CreatedById":126227,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T14:10:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380584\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526565201\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188977\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SoulReaper1702\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, SoulReaper1702 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what should I do val?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d try with a simpler wing layout to reduce the possible amount of faults.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nA simple straight wing, with optional Ailerons.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nOne set of horizontal fins at the back for elevator control\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nKeep the vertical fins as is.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nKeep the \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#00ffff;\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0close behind \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffff00;\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E as you have it now. If you can get that to work, you can add more and modify layout until you find out what made it go wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SoulReaper1702","CreatedById":188977,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T19:41:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526566206\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Val\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Val said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d try with a simpler wing layout to reduce the possible amount of faults.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nA simple straight wing, with optional Ailerons.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nOne set of horizontal fins at the back for elevator control\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nKeep the vertical fins as is.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nKeep the \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#00ffff;\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0close behind \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffff00;\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E as you have it now. If you can get that to work, you can add more and modify layout until you find out what made it go wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI idid so, however it did not help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeres pictures of the simpler wings\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhttps://drive.google.com/open?id=1Yupvwbu1Yk5mBkjn94Rad9eMrMyQ9mxm\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhttps://drive.google.com/open?id=1i0RcoeQ0-yhw5erRH821psg7tAOAOhCd\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526564120\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor some reason, I\u0027m not having that problem... You\u0027re probably right and I\u0027ve found some sort of strange KSP physics flaw...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny tips that may resolve the problem i have mate?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbonara","CreatedById":188602,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-17T21:06:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380150\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526503813\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188977\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SoulReaper1702\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/16/2018 at 5:50 PM, SoulReaper1702 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am having trouble with the pitch of my plane. The plane takes off perfectly however 3-4 seconds after launch the airplane tilts down. I have tried moving the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E but that doesnt seem to help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003ECan you post a pic of your craft?\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was not able to open it, can you post it somewhere else like imgur? I\u2019d love to help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-17T21:11:26Z\u0022 title=\u002205/17/2018 09:11  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 17, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbonara\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-19T08:27:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve had these problems before with swept wings. They just seem to cause any attached elevons to work upside-down - no matter how attached to wings or where they are mounted.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tend to avoid the swept wings or else never put elevons on them (you can attach them elsewhere and move them to look as though attached to the wings with shift-offset).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-19T08:34:33Z\u0022 title=\u002205/19/2018 08:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 19, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Foxster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}